-- Toyota sees 2007/08 global sales at 8.89 mln units
-- 
-- Wed May 9, 2007 6:42am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/09/us-toyota-results-sales-idUSTKB00271720070509

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp. ( 7203.T ) said on Wednesday it expects its group-based global vehicle sales for the 2007/08 business year to grow to 8.89 million units from the 8.524 million it sold last year. 

 Sales in North America are expected to come to 2.99 million units, up from 2.942 million, and 2.32 million units in Japan, up from 2.273 million units. The figures include sales at truck maker Hino Motors Ltd. ( 7205.T ) and compact car maker Daihatsu Motor Co. ( 7262.T ). Japan's top auto maker also said it is now assuming an average dollar rate of 115 yen and a euro rate of 150 yen in the business year to March 2008.